Vintage illustration of a person sitting at a wooden desk, arranging colorful square tiles on a cork board mounted on the wall. Each tile features a different abstract geometric symbol or pattern in warm oranges, teals, and cream colors. The scene is bathed in soft afternoon light coming through a nearby window with sheer curtains. The desk has an old brass lamp, scattered papers, and a steaming cup of coffee. The overall composition evokes 1950s mid-century modern aesthetic with slightly muted, warm color palette and subtle paper texture throughout. The tiles create a satisfying grid pattern, suggesting organization and personal curation of favorite destinations.
